g.text: describe how html elements are to be displayed.
selector : which element(s) you want to style.
-combinator selector(based on a specific relation between them)
-pseudo-elements selector (select and style a part of an element)
selects all elements of specific type
selects element with a specific class.
select single element with a specific id
Selects elements that are descendants of a specified element.
Selects direct children of a specified element.
Selects the element immediately following another element.
Selects all siblings following a specified element.
*Attribute Presence* [target] { } -> Selects elements with a specific attribute.
*Attribute Exact Value* [target="_blank"] { } -> Selects elements with a specific attribute and value.
*Attribute Contains Value* [class*="example"] { } -> Selects elements with an attribute containing a specific substring.
*Attribute Starts With* [href^="https"] { } -> Selects elements with an attribute starting with a specific value.
*Attribute Ends With* [src$=".jpg"] { } -> Selects elements with an attribute ending with a specific value.
*Attribute Contains Word* [class~="example"] { } -> Selects elements with an attribute containing a specific word.
*Hover* a:hover { } -> Selects an element when hovered.
*Focus* input:focus { } -> Selects an element when focused.
*First Child* p:first-child { } -> Selects the first child of a parent element.
*Last Child* p:last-child { } -> Selects the last child of a parent element.
*Nth Child* p:nth-child(2) { } -> Selects the nth child of a parent element.
*Not* :not(.class-name) { } -> Selects elements that do not match a selector.
*Before* p::before { content: "→"; } -> Inserts content before an element.
*After* p::after { content: "←"; } -> Inserts content after an element.
*First Letter* p::first-letter { } -> Selects the first letter of an element.
*First Line* p::first-line { } -> Selects the first line of an element.
*Grouping Selector* h1, h2, h3 { } -> Applies styles to multiple selectors.
*Empty* div:empty { } -> Selects elements with no children.
